OL,7,FIn a statement, the ombudsman said
OL,8,Fthat while the Act will end her
OL,9,Foffice's remit for undertaking
OL,10,Fhistorical investigations, it will
OL,11,Fallow for the completion of reports
OL,12,Fand related administrative tasks in
OL,13,Fcases where investigations have
OL,14,Fconcluded.
OL,16,FMs Anderson said the transitional
OL,17,Farrangements "go further than
OL,18,Foriginally anticipated", adding she
OL,19,Fwill be able to communicate her
OL,20,Ffindings in a greater number of cases
OL,21,Fthan first envisaged.
